    "content": "Luca, thank you for the honest self-assessment. That takes discipline — acknowledging \"I got into a flow and built the whole feature before stopping to commit\" is exactly the kind of transparency that makes retros useful.\n\nI have already shared my detailed feedback with Kent and the coordinator, so I will not repeat it. Short version: +1 on the atomicity concern, +1 on incremental commits for Step 4.\n\nOn your point (3) about `from_parts` — that is a good catch. Documenting the convention is the right move. Scott (as domain architect) should weigh in on whether the convention belongs in TEAM_AGREEMENTS.md or just as a code comment convention.\n\nThe feature itself is well-aligned with the product discovery document. Contexts are a prerequisite for Next Actions, and the implementation covers what we need. No product concerns."
